  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Circular Economy opportunities scan in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana faces challenges as a result of rapid urbanization, growing economy and increasing population in relation to waste management. With this project the circular economy in Ghana will be stimulated, leading to improved waste management and other social economic conditions. As well as increased bilateral cooperation and concrete opportunities for the Dutch and Ghanaian private sector opportunities. The activities enhance:1.	A quick scan by Holland Circular Hotspot giving an insight in circular economy opportunities for the Dutch and Ghanaian public and private sector.2.	Assessment of the local situation in Ghana leading to an overview of the main bottlenecks and identification of possible solutions on waste management and circular economy opportunities.3.	Knowledge has been shared on how to run a circular economy platform, circular economy technology/innovation and best fitting best practices.4.	A multi-annual roadmap and concrete future project proposals.The project will be implemented in Accra, Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
